 guidelines for improving negotiation performance today. The main ideas are relevant for any country and for all who may be affected by economic bargaining.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCommercial treaties. 0aInternational economic relations. 0aNegotiation in business. 4aGeneral Economics. 4aPolitical Science & Political History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150173205840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501732058423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501732058/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles